class-closed.help: Specifies whether additional properties that are not defined in the schema can be used in the data. If no, then these extra undefined properties are forbidden.
class-closed.title: Additional class properties

dematerialization.cardinality restriction: Only those associations that do not have a cardinality higher than 1 can be dematerialized.
dematerialization.help: By dematerializing the association, all elements of the referenced class are moved directly to the parent class. The association will then not be included in the diagram.
dematerialization.title: Dematerialization

empty as complex.checkbox: Treat class without content as reference
empty as complex.help: The default behavior of Dataspecer is that empty classes are interpreted as references - attributes of the IRI type with appropriate items. This setting allows treating an empty class as an empty complex type.
empty as complex.title: Empty class behavior

instancesSpecifyTypes.help: Specifies whether instances of classes must specify their type, that is, the class of which they are instances of. The disabled option then removes any auxiliary constructs for working with types from the artifacts.
instancesSpecifyTypes.title: Explicit instance typing

iri parameters help: Class instances (data) can be identified by their specific IRI. For example, Prague, as a city instance, can have its IRI http://example.com/Praha. This option sets whether such an identifier is required in the data, which affects the validation of the data and its representation in RDF, for example, where resources without IRIs appear as blank nodes.
JSON-LD IRI prefixes: Prefixes used in JSON-LD context and schemas
JSON-LD IRI prefixes help: The table below allows you to set frequently used prefixes for IRIs used in the JSON-LD context and thus for IRIs used in JSON Schemas.
JSON-LD type mapping help: In case of a collision between type names used in the JSON-LD context, you can set custom mapping of IRIs to type names here.

object examples.help text: Use JSON format to define example.

some translations other sources: Some of the translation may be from other resources.
